%U A396019 956250000,993750000,1031250000,1312500000,2031250000,2312500000,3031250000,3093750000,3312500000,3937500000,4031250000
%N A396019 Grand-grand-grand-kangaroo numbers: kangaroo numbers whose inner number is a grand-grand-kangaroo number (A395926).
%H A396019 David A. Corneth, <a href="/A396019/b396019.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10472</a> (terms <= 10^45)
%H A396019 Michael S. Branicky, <a href="/A396019/a396019_1.py.txt">Python program for OEIS A396019</a>
%H A396019 Carole Dubois, <a href="/A396019/a396019_1.jpg">Graphs for Kangaroos</a>
%H A396019 Mickaël Launay, <a href="https://www.lemonde.fr/sciences/article/2026/04/18/nombres-kangourous-l-enigme-maths-du-monde-n-97_6681126_1650684.html">Nombres kangourous, l’énigme maths du « Monde » nᵒ 97</a>
%e A396019 931250000 is a grand-grand-grand kangaroo number as a multiple of 3125000, 3125000 is itself a grand-grand kangaroo number as a multiple of 12500, 12500 is itself a grand kangaroo number as a multiple of 250 and 250 is a kangaroo number as a multiple of 5.
%o A396019 (Python)
%o A396019 def joey(n): return int(str(n)[1:-1]) if n > 99 else 0
%o A396019 def kangaroo(n): return n > 99 and (j:=joey(n)) > 0 and n%j == 0
%o A396019 def ok(n): return n > 9999999 and kangaroo(n) and kangaroo(j:=joey(n)) and kangaroo(jj:=joey(j)) and kangaroo(joey(jj))
%o A396019 # _Michael S. Branicky_, May 14 2026
%o A396019 (Python) # see linked program to produce b-file
